Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases state risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded in August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary", have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several ways.
The Institute's "Risk Warning Report" states, among other things, that in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk represents the "intensification of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic clashes in the short term".
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is presumably aimed at provoking such a dispute, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure on the part of the political leaders: "People of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups that have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungarian opposition."
It is suspected that this would exacerbate the problem, make reasonable dialogue impossible, favor limbs, and increase the likelihood of violent clashes.
The research institute also believes that the activities of the Hungarian Guards, not least thanks to the enormous attention from the domestic and foreign media, "have significantly damaged Hungary's image abroad, especially in terms of confidence in stability and democratic maturity".
We remember that since the autumn of 2006, the reorganization of radical and extreme right-wing groups in Hungary has been continuously on the rise, so that since the summer of 2007, several organizations called "national self-defense associations" have been founded.
“It is common for these groups to define themselves as a civilian organization, while bragging openly about preparing their members for – sometimes armed – defense tasks (disaster protection, national defense, security), citing the incapacity of the police, the army, or the state itself,” it said.
And furthermore, all this is done according to that method, which attempts to disguise various political aspirations as a bourgeois initiative based on the political and party resentment of the population.
The emphasis on civil character and the form of association are therefore not only used to circumvent legal hurdles that could arise in the course of registration in court - it is also a political strategy.
As can be seen from the analysis, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are also a risk-increasing factor in relations with neighbouring countries.
In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighbouring countries, as some ultra-nationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries see in the emergence of the Hungarian Guard the confirmation of its own anti-Hungarian policy.
All of this has an impact on the political stability of the region,” he said.
From the point of view of the research institute, the establishment of the Hungarian Guard is not an individual phenomenon in Central Eastern Europe, so the political risk for the entire region has increased.
As reported, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are comparable to those of the Bulgarian National Guard, whose foundation was announced in August 2007 by the far-right Bulgarian National Union (BNU).
