A driver’s license is a document in which everyone can decide whether to own it or not.
This is not an identity card that everyone, including a valid one, must have.
People who no longer want to drive should give up their driver's license.
It is sufficient to take him to the competent municipal office or to send him there by registered letter.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 become invalid.
However, drivers must also gradually exchange other types of driving licenses.
People with driving licenses from 1994 to 2000 have three years left to exchange.
The validity of driving licences issued from 2001 to 2004 expires in December 2013.
According to Hanzelka, there are about 2.6 million more driving licences.
