What are the circumstances of the accident?
According to the first results of the investigation of the National Disciplinary Authority of the Police (IGPN), on Sunday, shortly after 5 pm, a police car drove on Rue Louise-Michel towards Villiers-le-Bel.
He had no mission, but was on patrol, and drove at 40-50 km/h, without blue light, a spokesman for the police said.
A green motorcycle of the brand Kawasaki, without registration, i.e. not approved for public transport (see below), came, controlled by two teenagers without a helmet, approached at very high speed.
It rammed the left side of the police car after it disregarded its right-hand driveway, a policeman said.
The alcohol control carried out by the vehicle passengers is very negative.
The condition of the car (crumpled fender, splintered windshield, torn bumper) testifies to the severity of the impact.
Very quickly, already yesterday morning, the Prosecutor of the Republic of Pontoise, Marie-Thérèse de Givry, announced that she had entrusted the IGPN with an investigation into the "facts of involuntary killings and the lack of assistance to persons in danger", in consultation with the main public safety department of Val-d'Oise.
In the afternoon, on the occasion of a press conference, the prosecutor declared that she excludes the responsibility of the police officers to investigate the IGPN at this stage.
According to the magistrate, three witnesses to the accident, who were heard Sunday night, have confirmed the police’s version, namely that this small motorbike has reached their left side relatively quickly.
Yesterday, a kind of groove, certainly caused by the friction of the footrests on the ground, showed that the two vehicles had remained hooked to each other until the police managed to brake.
The vehicles have been confiscated and will be subject to a technical review.
The bodies of the two victims were obducted yesterday.
What happened next?
Yesterday in Villiers-le-Bel there was a rumor that the police had left the accident site very quickly, without helping the two young men.
Although the IGPN remains very cautious, it would also rule out any serious mistakes in this matter.
According to a police source, this is a difficult aspect of the investigation, for which further investigation is necessary, and in which it is necessary to proceed very carefully .
Libération met an eyewitness of these few moments shortly after the accident.
From one of his windows he had a direct view of the scene.
We immediately went out with my cousin, who is a nurse in the hospital, to try to revive her, says this witness.
There was nothing to do.
Then he saw a completely disturbed policeman lying down.
Two more tried to revive one of the youths, the fourth on the phone.
Given the tension that had quickly formed around the event and, it seems, due to the certainty that the people present had about the unexpected situation of the young people, the policemen were taken in the car by colleagues who had arrived at the accident site.
Still, according to this testimony, the rescuers arrived about twenty minutes after the policemen left.
They have also used cardiac massages, but in vain.
I will not allow any claim to be made that the police forces did not help the young people.
First aid was given to these young people.
The fire brigade arrived immediately.
Everything was done to try to save her, the prosecutor stressed.
