The Bank of England takes note of the concern, offering 10 billion pounds for five weeks
The Bank of England on Thursday expressed concern about curbing the ongoing worry over lending conditions, announcing a <0xC2><0xA3>10 billion offer at a base rate of 5.75% for five weeks, an unusually long-term offer.
To alleviate the fears that financial market conditions will be particularly difficult at the end of the year, and to give banks greater certainty about the way in which they should organise their liquidity positions during this period, the Bank intends to offer a significant portion of their savings deposits during the maintenance phase, which begins on 6 December, in the form of an open-market notification for five weeks.
The Bank further explains that in this way, 10 billion pounds (14 billion euros) will be in circulation on December 6 at 12.15 GMT, at the basic tax rate and only until January 10.
