Is the stock market ahead of a final year rally? Expert disagreement due to the US mortgage crisis
With just under five weeks until the end of the year on the stock market, investors are already rubbing their hands with a view to the coming end-year rally.
Nevertheless, the experts cannot make reliable forecasts in this regard.
Banif believes that purely statistically speaking, the month of December on the stock market is usually associated with a positive market development.
Nonetheless, it is not advisable to make forecasts in the short term and only on the basis of statistics. Especially not when serious tensions determine the current market developments.
Although other experts do not approve of such a strong price increase in the final weeks of the year, they note that the stock market price is determined by the given liquidity of the market and the market participants, who invest mainly in pension funds due to the lack of safe equity funds, which is strongly affected by the upward trend towards profitable assets.
As a result, according to these experts, the stock market will have a rather lateral price trend, influenced by market fluctuations, especially since we cannot yet estimate the extent of the possible decline in the Fed’s interest rate, an uncertainty that is mainly due to the rise in crude oil prices and the risk of the rise in inflation rate.
Javier Barrio, chairman of BPI’s sales department in Spain, agrees that it is a bold time to announce an upcoming market rally.
The chances are not very good, the expert assures.
The Spanish stock index Ibex has already lost a value of 4% since its peak on November 8 of 15,945.7 points.
But not all experts share the same negative opinion.
According to Juan Solana, an analyst at Intermoney, the Ibex 35 could successfully end the year with almost 16,000 points as a result of the restructuring of the investment funds and the traditional grants made each year around this time.
Nevertheless, the expert points out that this year things could be going a little differently, mainly due to the end-year rally taking place in the second week of December, and thus directly after Bridge Day to Constitution Day.
In the analyst’s view, price fluctuations would not affect market trends.
According to Federico Olucha, an analyst at Bank Inversis, previous assessments of the market situation are at a near-technical level, which could result in a deviation from the index values, the extent of which depends on the consequences of the U.S. mortgage market crisis.
The analyst trusts that these will be positive.
Analysts agree on the selection of the values that will push the Ibex to new heights.
Solana of Intermoney says that this year the big values are the turn.
Among the value winners, the expert would include the two major banks and some real estate companies, as the electricity sector will be too expensive at the given time.
Meanwhile, Federico Olucha of Bank Inversis assures that the increases will be associated with the banking and industrial sectors.
