Regarding the increased consumption behavior during the Christmas days, periodic consumption will determine the market in the last half of the year.
On the other hand, the expert believes that the technologies will also achieve positive sales results, even if they are only represented in small numbers in the Spanish market.
Five times in seven years
In the last seven years, December has seen only two declines.
When the technology bubble burst at the end of 2003, this led the stock market out of its crisis and at the same time initiated the last real end-year rally so far.
This year, when the Ibex 35 picked up 28.17 percentage points, December saw a price increase of 6.68%.
Whether 2008 will be the fifth profitable year in a row (the Ibex rises by 8.36% since January) and also a final year rally will be shown.
