Congress agrees to the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
Parallel to the parliamentary drafting, which ended its session today with the decision of Congress in the Senate on the amendments/additions associated with the project, the government published the provisions resulting from the new law with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senators, who had pursued in their negotiations and votes the objective of establishing the best possible regulation that ensures the safety of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities in order to guarantee a generally efficient market operation.
In addition to the modernisation of financial markets, the MIFID, which re-establishes the Securities Services Regulation, aims to improve investor protection, increase the control entitlement of the Spanish Securities Commission (CNMV) and promote cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive makes it possible to offer financial advice to both specialised firms and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services firms (ESIS), the advisory firms that partner with investment and brokerage firms.
In addition, it expands the number of financial transaction execution systems, adding to the regulated circulation markets the multilateral systems of effect trading and the systems for the internationalization of trade orders, which would eventually compete with the current economic players.
The law obliges investment firms to disclose the focal points of their corporate profile, the confrontation and ways of dealing with risks in the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Congressional Economic Commission foresees further changes in hindsight, with the decision that the securities bond must now be considered complex financial resources for the investor due to its high level of risk, confirmed by the U.S. mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the working areas of graduate economists was used; 30 years after 1977, the regulation was adopted restricting the working areas reserved for economists.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on behalf of others, does not need authorization from the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialization of products and for the acquisition of customers at the same time to several investment companies.
