Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of drawing up of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance policyholder.
This agreement is entered into in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and is obliged in return to submit the corresponding amount of compensation in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance, which is composed of several factors, including age, gender, date of issue of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that if there is a higher risk of accident, higher contribution payments will also be due.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contribution payments, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since according to the statistical values and accordingly also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that most likely meets his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that one should consider when choosing an insurance in order to make not only a performance- but also a price-oriented choice.
Those under 25 years of age face numerous obstacles when choosing a low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and a young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for ideal insurance coverage to take out full insurance, there are nonetheless cheaper alternatives.
The cautious drivers can choose a full insurance with a deductible, so that while the benefits of a full insurance are covered, they are offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred by the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the contract is concluded and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, main representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance brokerage company.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against damage to their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under the age of 25, it is up to you to reduce insurance costs, thus increasing your credit by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction of the basic rate with the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in said tariffs.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase bonus payments, Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, which is due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Therefore, it is most sensible to opt for full insurance with self-equity.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving , explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second practice year after the fear of the beginner has been removed.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person also allows.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, the best option would be a full insurance with a deductible (with an amount of around 300 euros). In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which starts only for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, notes Luis Noguera.
For retirees, it is advisable to take out a full insurance with self-eligibility (at an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only starts with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accidental damage, but also because it carries high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
